# T-2189 — /preflight doc-set drift nightly canary (catches Check-N
# enumeration desync across the 4 canonical surfaces: script docstring,
# CLAUDE.md catalog row, .claude/commands/preflight.md skill, and
# docs/operations/substrate-cron-recipes.md).
#
# Source of truth: /opt/termlink/.context/cron/preflight-doc-set-drift-canary.crontab (git-tracked)
# Installed to:    /etc/cron.d/termlink-preflight-doc-set-drift-canary (USER field syntax — do NOT load into a user crontab)
#
# Closes the structural prevention gap exposed by T-2185/T-2186/T-2187:
# each was a same-day doc-sync follow-up that existed because a new
# Check N was added in one surface but not the other three. The drift
# detector (scripts/check-preflight-doc-set-drift.sh, T-2188) catches
# that class; this cron runs it nightly so the next drift episode is
# operator-visible before anyone reads the stale surface.
#
# Exit 0 from --quiet means PASS; the log accumulates only when surfaces
# disagree on the claimed check count, so an empty log is the healthy
# state. /canaries auto-discovers this log file via the .*-canary.log
# glob (T-2172) so operators see it surface alongside the other cron
# canaries without explicit registration.
#
# Diagnostic on log entry: read the diagnostic table — it shows each
# surface's claimed count side-by-side, with `<-- DRIFT` markers on the
# outliers. Resync per T-2185/T-2186/T-2187 per-surface edit pattern.
#
# Operator action when fired: pick the authoritative source (typically
# the script docstring's `Check N:` enumeration), bring the other three
# surfaces into agreement, then verify with
# `bash scripts/check-preflight-doc-set-drift.sh` (verbose).
SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

# Daily at 05:53 UTC — minute offset chosen to dodge all known canaries:
# :13 mirror, :17 heartbeat, :23 substrate-preflight, :33 mirror-meta,
# :43 rollout-audit, :53 (this). Runs as root so cwd-into the repo is
# cheap and the .log file's owner matches the substrate-preflight
# canary's owner (operator inspection convention).
53 5 * * * root cd /opt/termlink && bash scripts/check-preflight-doc-set-drift.sh --quiet >> .context/working/.preflight-doc-set-drift-canary.log 2>&1

# T-2193 — meta-canary. Fires ~50 minutes after the canary above on a
# different minute so a load-time race or transient cron lock can't take
# both out together. Reuses scripts/check-canary-aliveness.sh (T-1723
# parameterized in T-2175) via env-var overrides. --quiet means the log
# only grows when check-preflight-doc-set-drift.sh's heartbeat is stale;
# an empty log here is the healthy state (same convention as the canary
# it watches). Offset chosen to dodge known canaries: :13 mirror,
# :17 heartbeat, :23 substrate-preflight, :33 mirror-meta,
# :43 substrate-preflight-meta / rollout-audit, :53 (canary above).
# Probe runs the drift detector itself with --no-heartbeat so the
# freshness probe doesn't side-effect the very signal it's checking.
43 7 * * * root cd /opt/termlink && HEARTBEAT_FILE=.context/working/.preflight-doc-set-drift-canary.heartbeat CANARY_NAME="preflight-doc-set-drift canary" CANARY_PROBE_CMD="bash scripts/check-preflight-doc-set-drift.sh --quiet --no-heartbeat" CANARY_CRON_PATH=/etc/cron.d/termlink-preflight-doc-set-drift-canary bash scripts/check-canary-aliveness.sh --quiet >> .context/working/.canary-aliveness.log 2>&1
